Four people have been reportedly shot dead and about six critically injured following a taxi-related violence incident in Brakpan CBD, Ekurhuleni on Wednesday. The violence is alleged to have started from Tuesday in the Tsakane area. Members of a taxi association are alleged to have moved from Tsakane cluster and clashed with members of the Greater Brakpan Taxi Association. The police said that seven suspects have been arrested. WARNING!!! Reports… 3 people killed and 10 injured in a taxi shooting that happened in Brakpan. No taxis operational for the safety of commuters. Commuters will be be updated as the situation improves. — SANTACO (@SA_Taxis) May 23, 2018  More details to follow -Afro Voice Reporter 